Picks Jerry Uhuo As Special Adviser On Policy And Strategy ABUJA – The House of Representatives’ Speaker, Honourable Tajudeen Abbas, has appointed former National Assembly Correspondent with the Daily Trust newspaper, Musa Abdullahi Krishi, as his Special Adviser on Media and Publicity. The Speaker also announced the appointment of Dr Jerry Uhuo as special Adviser on Policy and Strategy. The appointments which take immediate effect from Wednesday June 15, 2023 was contained in a statement personally signed by the Speaker on Thursday in Abuja. The new Special Adviser to the Speaker on Media and Publicity was also the Chief Press Secretary (CPS), to the immediate past Speaker of the House, Femi Gbajabiamila. The statement reads: “I am pleased to announce the appointment of Musa Abdullahi Krishi as my Special Adviser on Media and Publicity. The appointment takes immediate effect.” “Musa Abdulahi Krishi has several years of experience in legislative reporting, covering both the House and the Senate at different times for the Daily Trust and is well acquainted with legislative nuances. “A graduate of Mass Communication from the famous Kaduna Polytechnic, Krishi joined Daily Trust as the Best Graduating Student of Mass Communication in 2012 as part of the newspaper’s policy. Between 2014 and 2015, he served as the Assistant Political Editor at the Daily Trust and became a senior correspondent. POLL “Krishi, who hails from Nasarawa State, also holds a Postgraduate Diploma in Mass Communication from the Bayero University, Kano (BUK), where he graduated as the best student of his set with a Distinction. “He served as the Chief Press Secretary to the immediate past Speaker of the 9th House, Rt. Hon. Femi Gbajabiamila, from 2019 to 2023. “The new spokesman, an associate of the Nigerian Institute of Public Relations (NIPR), is expected to bring his wealth of experience acquired over the years on board in line with the Legislative Agenda of the 10th House of Representatives.”